<lb n="1"/>svasti sakābdaṁbulu 1066 
<lb n="2"/>gu nēṇṭi kuṁbha <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/> yu bu 
<lb n="3" break="no"/>dhavāramuna nāvapalli nīlī 
<lb n="4" break="no"/>śvaradēvaraku <unclear>ma</unclear>ttana Eṟ<unclear>ku</unclear>maṁḍa 
<lb n="5" break="no"/>likuṁḍu peṭṭina Akhaṇḍavatti dīpa 
<lb n="6" break="no"/>vīṇṭi māḍa<unclear>5</unclear>nnu <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/> rivāru 
<lb n="7"/>[Ācaṁ]drārkamu naḍapaṁgalavā 
<lb n="8" break="no"/><unclear>ru</unclear> <gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/> 
</p>

<p><hi rend="italic">Note:</hi>—This inscription bears no number in the <hi rend="italic">Annual Report.</hi> As it appears to be engraved on the same pillar as No. 691, it is numbered here as 691-A.</p>

